===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|土|成|c1=s|c2=p|t1=soil|ls=psc}}, since city walls were originally made of stamped earth.

===Etymology===
Cognate with {{och-l|成|to complete; city walls}}, {{och-l|盛|id=1|to hold with a receptacle}}, {{och-l|盛|id=2|abundant; flourishing}}, as {{och-l|城|city wall}} was made of filled-in or stamped earth ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). See {{zh-l|*成}} for more.

Its original meaning was "city walls" and was originally written as [[成]]; later, it started to indicate the city (i.e., the part of territory within the city walls) due to [[metonymy]] since a single part of a city indicates the city itself.

